        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>
                <emph render="italic">Science &amp; Society</emph>, is a scholarly Marxist quarterly (1936- ) then and for many years thereafter associated with the Communist Party USA. The journal is interdisciplinary, applying a Marxist perspective to a broad range of topics; however, political economy is the most frequently represented topic, followed by Marxist philosophy, the history of communist movements, and other topics.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>This collection consists of files from the editorial staff of 
                <emph render="italic">Science &amp; Society</emph>. Most of the files are author files, which have correspondence to and from the authors, as well as, and usually, submitted manuscripts, regardless of whether or not they were published. There are other folders labeled correspondence, presumably concerning business, management, policy and political matters.</p>
            <p>FOR MORE INFORMATION, CONTACT: peter.filardo@nyu.edu</p>
        </scopecontent>
